<title>USA: Coke to boost investment in Russia.</title>
<headline>Coke to boost investment in Russia.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK</dateline>
<text>
<p>Coca-Cola Co. said Monday it plans to invest an additional $100 million in Russia by the end of 1997, boosting the total of its investment in the country to $600 million.</p>
<p>The company said the money will be used to build, upgrade and expand bottling and distribution operations throughout Russia.</p>
<p>Coca-Cola said it is now the leading soft-drink producer in 14 of the 15 former Soviet republics.</p>
